<subSubSection id="5CF6589A920FFFC8FF08FB41EDD6FA7E" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="14530B11920FFFC8FF08FB41EDD6FA7E" blockId="8.[131,776,1233,1495]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">REVISED DIAGNOSIS. — Microporid with erect colonies, narrow cylindrical branches lacking complete bifurcations, colonies probably articulated; autozooids lacking a gymnocyst, cryptocyst depressed centrally, pierced by 2 large opesiules; orifice subcircular to dummy shaped with a raised rim; no spines or tubercles; ovicells clustered resulting in branch dilation, ooecia helmet-shaped, continuous with cryptocysts of the distal zooids, orifices of fertile zooids enlarged; mandibulate polymorphs in some species, infrequent, larger than autozooids but with similar frontal wall and opesiules, orifice semielliptical, longer than wide.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5CF6589A920FFFC8FF08F980E8B2FC99" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="14530B11920FFFC8FF08F980ECA8F984" blockId="8.[132,776,1555,2028]" box="[132,232,1555,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920FFFC8FF08F9A1EE12F8E2" blockId="8.[132,776,1555,2028]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FF70F9A1ED90F9E5" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[252,464,1586,1612]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FF70F9A1ED90F9E5" box="[252,464,1586,1612]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the zooidal dimorphism evident in the 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B3920FFFC8FEE1F9C0EDDBF9C4" box="[365,411,1619,1645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus. In addition to normal autozooids (“Cellules A” of 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FDA9F9E0ECFDF905" author="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M." pageId="8" pageNumber="521" pagination="155 - 157" refId="ref7235" refString="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M. 1960. - Dimorphomicropora: nouveau genre de bryozoaire cheilostome du Maestrichtien du bassin aquitain. Compte Rendu de la Societe geologique de France 6: 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1960">Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux 1960</bibRefCitation>
), there are occasional polymorphic zooids (“Cellules B” of 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FF46F920EDB1F965" author="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M." box="[202,497,1714,1741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" pagination="155 - 157" refId="ref7235" refString="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M. 1960. - Dimorphomicropora: nouveau genre de bryozoaire cheilostome du Maestrichtien du bassin aquitain. Compte Rendu de la Societe geologique de France 6: 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1960">Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux 1960</bibRefCitation>
) with an enlarged orifice and presumably an enlarged operculum or mandible. These mandibulate polymorphs resemble the B-zooids found in 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FF0AF881ED54F885" authorityName="Smitt" authorityYear="1873" box="[134,276,1810,1836]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Steginoporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FF0AF881ED54F885" box="[134,276,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Steginoporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Like the B-zooids of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FD9DF881EEDFF885" authorityName="Smitt" authorityYear="1873" box="[529,671,1810,1836]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Steginoporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FD9DF881EEDFF885" box="[529,671,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Steginoporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it seems possible that they had the capacity to feed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920FFFC8FF17F8C2E9E3FD99" blockId="8.[132,776,1555,2028]" lastBlockId="8.[811,1457,215,816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">
The existence of mandibulate polymorphs in 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FDF9F8C2EC8FF822" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FDF9F8C2EC8FF822" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has led to the suggestion that this Cretaceous genus belongs to the Cenozoic family 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FE55F802EED7F802" box="[473,663,1937,1963]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="family">Steginoporellidae</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FF08F822ED2CF862" author="OSTROVSKY A. N." box="[132,364,1969,1996]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" refId="ref7998" refString="OSTROVSKY A. N. 2013. - Evolution of Sexual Reproduction in Marine Invertebrates. Example of Gymnolaemate Bryozoans. Springer, Dordrecht, 356 p. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 007 - 7146 - 8" type="book" year="2013">Ostrovsky (2013: 329)</bibRefCitation>
believed 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FE4AF822EECFF862" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[454,655,1969,1995]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FE4AF822EECFF862" box="[454,655,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be probably an unrelated homeomorph of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FE67F842EE37F842" authorityName="Smitt" authorityYear="1873" box="[491,631,2001,2027]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Steginoporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FE67F842EE37F842" box="[491,631,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Steginoporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and excluded it from his superorder 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FB87FF44E882FF58" authorityName="Ostrovsky" authorityYear="2013" box="[1035,1218,215,241]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" rank="superOrder" superOrder="Thalamoporellina">Thalamoporellina</taxonomicName>
to which 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FAA8FF44E9EDFF58" authorityName="Smitt" authorityYear="1873" box="[1316,1453,215,241]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Steginoporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FAA8FF44E9EDFF58" box="[1316,1453,215,241]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Steginoporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned. 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FC3CFF6BE8A7FEBB" author="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M." box="[944,1255,247,274]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" pagination="155 - 157" refId="ref7235" refString="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M. 1960. - Dimorphomicropora: nouveau genre de bryozoaire cheilostome du Maestrichtien du bassin aquitain. Compte Rendu de la Societe geologique de France 6: 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1960">Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux (1960)</bibRefCitation>
hypothesised that 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FCA2FE8BEFCCFE98" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[814,908,280,305]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="voigti">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FCA2FE8BEFCCFE98" box="[814,908,280,305]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">D. voigti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be an evolutionary link between 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FAC9FE8BEF2DFEF8" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="rugica">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FAC9FE8BEF2DFEF8" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Micropora rugica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[since assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FBB8FEA4E946FEF8" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[1076,1286,311,337]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FBB8FEA4E946FEF8" box="[1076,1286,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FAA1FEA4E9E6FEFB" author="VOIGT E." box="[1325,1446,311,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" pagination="77 - 95" refId="ref8472" refString="VOIGT E. 1975. - Heteromorphy in Cretaceous Bryozoa. Documents des Laboratoires de Geologie de la Faculte des Sciences de Lyon, Hors Serie 3: 77 - 95." type="journal article" year="1975">Voigt 1975</bibRefCitation>
] and 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FCD0FEC4E85AFED8" box="[860,1050,343,369]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="family">Steginoporellidae</taxonomicName>
. At the time of their publication, this was consistent with the stratigraphy because the 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B3920FFFC8FAA2FEE4E91CFE38" box="[1326,1372,375,401]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">type</typeStatus>
locality (Meschers, Charente-Maritime) of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FB14FE04E8B1FE19" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[1176,1265,407,432]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="voigti">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FB14FE04E8B1FE19" box="[1176,1265,407,432]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">D. voigti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered to be of middle Maastrichtian age, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FB5FFE24E972FE79" box="[1235,1330,439,464]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="rugica">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FB5FFE24E972FE79" box="[1235,1330,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">D. rugica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known only from the early Maastrichtian. However, the re-dating of Meschers as Campanian makes the order of occurrence of these two species incongruent with this evolutionary hypothesis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B11920FFFC8FCCFFDA5E8B2FC99" blockId="8.[811,1457,215,816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FCCFFDA5EF8CFDF8" author="VOIGT E." box="[835,972,566,593]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" pagination="77 - 95" refId="ref8472" refString="VOIGT E. 1975. - Heteromorphy in Cretaceous Bryozoa. Documents des Laboratoires de Geologie de la Faculte des Sciences de Lyon, Hors Serie 3: 77 - 95." type="journal article" year="1975">Voigt (1975)</bibRefCitation>
misunderstood the nature of the dimorphism described in 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FC4CFDC5E8D8FDD9" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[960,1176,598,624]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FC4CFDC5E8D8FDD9" box="[960,1176,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FB49FDC5EF38FD39" author="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M." pageId="8" pageNumber="521" pagination="155 - 157" refId="ref7235" refString="DUCASSE J. &amp; VIGNEAUX M. 1960. - Dimorphomicropora: nouveau genre de bryozoaire cheilostome du Maestrichtien du bassin aquitain. Compte Rendu de la Societe geologique de France 6: 155 - 157." type="journal article" year="1960">Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, interpreting it to refer to the contrast between nonbrooding and brooding ovicellate autozooids. However, the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FB9BFD26E8A6FD66" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[1047,1254,693,719]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FB9BFD26E8A6FD66" box="[1047,1254,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Dimorphomicropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes no mention of brooding zooids or ovicells. The 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B3920FFFC8FB2CFD45E88EFD59" box="[1184,1230,726,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FAD7FD45E86CFCB9" authority="(Ducasse, 1958)" baseAuthorityName="Ducasse" baseAuthorityYear="1958" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crustulenta">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FAD7FD45EF36FCA6" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">D. crustulenta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E0920FFFC8FC08FD66E864FCB9" author="DUCASSE J." box="[900,1060,757,784]" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" refId="ref7196" refString="DUCASSE J. 1958. - Les Bryozoaires maestrichtiens et campaniens de la Saintonge et du Perigord occidental, repartition et valeur stratigraphique. Travaux scientifiques du Centre de Geologie Approfondie, Universite de Bordeaux, 168 p." type="book" year="1958">Ducasse, 1958</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is ovicellate (
<figureCitation id="8CD71794920FFFC8FB32FD66E951FCB9" box="[1214,1297,757,784]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,932,949]" captionTargetBox="[133,1454,215,890]" captionTargetId="figure-495@10.[132,794,213,722]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 4. — Dimorphomicropora crestulata (Ducasse, 1958): A, holotype (Ducasse 1958: pl. 7, fig. 3), UB C.B.917 Ducasse Collection, probably Barbezieux Fm (foram biozone CVI), RN 730, close to police station, Mirambeau, Charente-Maritime, dilated branch with ovicellate zooids; B, C, NHMUK PI BZ 8271, Aubeterre Fm,cliff north of town,Meschers,Charente-Maritime;B, well-preserved branch;C, detail of autozooids;D, NHMUK PI BZ 8272, Aubeterre Fm,cliff north of town, Meschers, branch. Scale bars: A, 500 μm; B, C, D, 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6564685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6564685/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
), as is a poorly preserved specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC7092920FFFC8FBADFC85E83DFC86" authorityName="Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux" authorityYear="1960" box="[1057,1149,790,815]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="521" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="voigti">
<emphasis id="2698D703920FFFC8FBADFC85E83DFC86" box="[1057,1149,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">D. voigti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="8CD71794920FFFC8FB01FC86E8A4FC99" box="[1165,1252,789,816]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1512,1529]" captionTargetBox="[131,1454,216,1469]" captionTargetId="figure-169@9.[697,1266,752,1291]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 3. — Dimorphomicropora voigti Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux,1960: A, lectotype, UB C.B.993 (Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux 1960: fig. 1), probably Aubeterre Fm, Meschers, Charente-Maritime, branch with large polymorphic zooid near base; B, E, F, NHMUK PI BZ 8767, Aubeterre Fm, Pointe de Suzac, Meschers; B, branch; E, autozooids near base of branch; F, detail of an orifice; C, G, NHMUK PI BZ 8768, Aubeterre Fm, Pointe de Suzac, Meschers; C, branch with a large polymorphic zooid near the centre; G, detail of polymorph; D, paralectotype, UB C.B.994 (Ducasse &amp; Vigneaux 1960: fig. 2), probably Aubeterre Fm, Meschers, Charente- Maritime; H, NHMUK PI BZ 8769, Aubeterre Fm, Pointe de Suzac, Meschers, Charente-Maritime, dilated branch with a cluster of ovicellate zooids. Scale bars: A, B, C, D, H, 500 μm; E, 200 μm; F, G, 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6564681" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6564681/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="521">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
